disabled, and LGBT individuals are denied technologies available to well-off nonminority heterosexual applicants. An original argument on a highly emotional and important issue, this work offers a surprising departure from more familiar arguments on the issue as it warns physicians, government agencies, and the general public against repeating the mistakes of the past.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aDiscrimination in medical carexLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aDiscrimination in medical carezUnited States. 0aHuman reproductive technologyxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aHuman reproductive technologyxSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aLAW / Medical Law & Legislation.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2018z9783110603156oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300229035423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300229035.jpg  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-063898-1  YUP eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017